1
00:00:01,020 --> 00:00:08,220
♪

2
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,220
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:10,220 --> 00:01:45,060
♪

4
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,250
Nine-Headed Dragon Flash!

5
00:01:48,250 --> 00:01:50,250
(yelling)

6
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:54,250
♪

7
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:56,100
(gasps)

8
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:58,220
(labored breathing)

9
00:01:58,220 --> 00:02:16,250
♪

10
00:02:16,250 --> 00:02:18,140
What the hell's going on?

11
00:02:18,140 --> 00:02:19,170
There's fire everywhere,

12
00:02:19,170 --> 00:02:22,150
it's burning
everything in its path!

13
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:24,080
It's a reflection
of Shishio's rage.

14
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:26,030
It's reacting to him
like the leaves reacted

15
00:02:26,030 --> 00:02:27,080
to Kenshin.

16
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:28,130
Not quite.

17
00:02:28,130 --> 00:02:30,170
I think that Shishio's
totally out of control.

18
00:02:30,170 --> 00:02:33,090
Are you ready for
the final encounter?

19
00:02:33,090 --> 00:02:39,210
♪

20
00:02:39,210 --> 00:02:40,290
You're alive!

21
00:02:40,290 --> 00:02:44,180
Behold the secret sword
technique of Kaguzuchi!

22
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:46,070
(labored breathing)

23
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:57,170
(flames roaring)

24
00:03:12,230 --> 00:03:14,200
(heavy breathing)

25
00:03:22,150 --> 00:03:24,120
(groaning)

26
00:03:39,270 --> 00:03:42,050
♪

27
00:03:48,260 --> 00:03:51,200
That's the stance
he uses for Amakakeru.

28
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,260
So what if it is?

29
00:03:52,260 --> 00:03:54,020
Just look at him.

30
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:56,170
He's too badly injured
to be of any danger.

31
00:03:56,170 --> 00:03:59,070
Even if he tries,
Himura's Amakakeru secret

32
00:03:59,070 --> 00:04:01,010
is already known
to Mr. Shishio.

33
00:04:01,010 --> 00:04:03,080
Even though Sojiro
lost to Himura,

34
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:06,010
he learned the secret
and told Mr. Shishio.

35
00:04:06,010 --> 00:04:07,040
♪

36
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,090
Come on.

37
00:04:08,090 --> 00:04:16,120
♪

38
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:18,140
The key to the Amakakeru
is a certain movement

39
00:04:18,140 --> 00:04:19,230
of Himura's left foot.

40
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:22,090
When Mr. Shishio sees that,
he'll know it's coming

41
00:04:22,090 --> 00:04:23,280
and he'll be able to block it.

42
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:37,010
♪

43
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:39,290
I admit, it's been
an enjoyable battle.

44
00:04:39,290 --> 00:04:43,150
I haven't fought anyone
this good for a long time.

45
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:45,010
But I have the whole
country to conquer

46
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:46,200
and don't have much time,

47
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:49,140
so I'm afraid I'm going to
have to end this fight quickly.

48
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:51,060
♪

49
00:04:51,060 --> 00:04:53,010
You're right about one thing.

50
00:04:53,010 --> 00:04:54,090
It's been a long fight,

51
00:04:54,090 --> 00:04:56,270
the time has come to end it
one way or another.

52
00:04:56,270 --> 00:04:58,130
I don't care if I win or lose

53
00:04:58,130 --> 00:05:00,050
as long as I do my best.

54
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:02,160
But if you win, the lives
of millions of innocent people

55
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:06,010
will be ruined and that's
why I have to stop you.

56
00:05:06,010 --> 00:05:08,140
You're welcome to try
but you'll never stop me

57
00:05:08,140 --> 00:05:10,240
as long as I can
hold this sword.

58
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:12,100
♪

59
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:14,020
And I'll never stop trying

60
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:17,000
as long as I can hold
mine, Shishio Makoto.

61
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:32,100
♪

62
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,250
Come on.

63
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:35,100
Let's do it.

64
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:38,080
♪

65
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,260
Ya!

66
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:41,230
(birds chirping)

67
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,270
Everything's so badly damaged,

68
00:05:48,270 --> 00:05:51,000
I don't know if we'll
ever get it cleaned up.

69
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:51,379
What?

70
00:05:51,379 --> 00:05:53,150
You call this badly damaged?

71
00:05:53,150 --> 00:05:56,050
This is nothing compared
to what it was like last time.

72
00:05:56,050 --> 00:05:57,230
We'll have this mess cleaned up

73
00:05:57,230 --> 00:05:59,230
and everything'll
be back to normal.

74
00:05:59,230 --> 00:06:02,210
'Course, we have a little
remodeling to do here and there

75
00:06:02,210 --> 00:06:05,030
but that'll make it
nicer than before.

76
00:06:05,030 --> 00:06:06,250
(laughing)

77
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:09,160
I just don't want you pushing
yourself too hard, that's all.

78
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:12,150
You're not as young or strong
as you used to be, you know?

79
00:06:12,150 --> 00:06:13,210
Oh yeah, says who?

80
00:06:13,210 --> 00:06:15,180
They don't call me
"Tiger" for nothing.

81
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:17,030
Whoa!

82
00:06:17,030 --> 00:06:18,170
Here's the water
you asked for, Kori.

83
00:06:18,170 --> 00:06:20,020
Thanks, Omasu.

84
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:23,130
(grunting)

85
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:24,180
Okina!

86
00:06:24,180 --> 00:06:25,240
Will you please
stop goofing around

87
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,240
and help me clean up?

88
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:28,240
We've got a lot
of work to do...

89
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,250
Tiger.

90
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:31,030
Could you help me?

91
00:06:31,030 --> 00:06:32,080
You got yourself up there,

92
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,090
you can get yourself down.

93
00:06:34,090 --> 00:06:36,220
Thanks a heap, oh!

94
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:37,260
Kori!

95
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:39,100
You're worried
about him, aren't you?

96
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:40,130
Huh?

97
00:06:40,130 --> 00:06:42,160
You don't have to
worry about Kenshin.

98
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:44,260
As long as he uses the
secret fighting technique

99
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:45,290
that I taught him,

100
00:06:45,290 --> 00:06:48,090
he can not ever
be defeated in battle.

101
00:06:48,090 --> 00:06:51,070
Even if an opponent avoids
the jaws of the dragon,

102
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:53,130
the wind of its passage
will render him helpless

103
00:06:53,130 --> 00:06:56,130
and he'll be
torn apart by its claws.

104
00:06:56,130 --> 00:06:58,130
Of course,
that's assuming that...

105
00:06:58,130 --> 00:06:59,150
(slurps)

106
00:06:59,150 --> 00:07:00,230
...he's in perfect condition.

107
00:07:00,230 --> 00:07:02,140
But if he's badly
wounded to begin with,

108
00:07:02,140 --> 00:07:05,130
his technique won't do
him a damn bit of good.

109
00:07:05,130 --> 00:07:07,260
Have I told you lately
how pretty you are?

110
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:09,030
Mm-hm.

111
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:10,130
(giggles)

112
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:12,050
I'm not that worried.

113
00:07:12,050 --> 00:07:13,200
Kenshin's going to win

114
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,070
and come back safe and sound.

115
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:18,270
Right, and the same
goes for Aoshi.

116
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:21,130
It won't be long before
he comes back again.

117
00:07:22,290 --> 00:07:27,110
Yup, then we'll be together
forever till the end of time.

118
00:07:27,110 --> 00:07:28,270
I don't understand you.

119
00:07:28,270 --> 00:07:31,130
How can you be in love
with such a weirdo?

120
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:32,280
(yelling)

121
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,220
Right now you're not
old enough to understand

122
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:36,260
what love is all about, Yoshi.

123
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:38,130
It's different for everyone.

124
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:39,150
Ask a hundred people

125
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:41,200
and you'd get a hundred
different answers.

126
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,160
That's one of the
great things about love

127
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:45,110
that makes it so wonderful.

128
00:07:45,110 --> 00:07:47,080
(grunting)

129
00:07:49,020 --> 00:07:51,080
Take that, you little brat!

130
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:54,270
I know you'll
come back, Kenshin.

131
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:56,290
I know...

132
00:07:56,290 --> 00:07:59,270
that you'll keep your promise.

133
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:06,260
♪

134
00:08:06,260 --> 00:08:07,290
Yeah!

135
00:08:07,290 --> 00:08:12,110
♪

136
00:08:12,110 --> 00:08:13,160
Shishio!

137
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:16,010
Don't worry, Kenshin
doesn't have a chance.

138
00:08:16,010 --> 00:08:17,230
(laughing diabolically)

139
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:21,260
♪

140
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:24,040
Mr. Shishio is using
his secret technique.

141
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:26,120
Himura will be destroyed.

142
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:28,120
(laughing)

143
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:32,070
♪

144
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:34,050
Huh?

145
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:37,040
I avoided the first blow
of his secret technique

146
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:38,250
but his sword strike
is so powerful

147
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:40,220
that it created a vortex,

148
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:43,010
a zone of rushing air so strong,

149
00:08:43,010 --> 00:08:45,260
it's like trying to fight
the force of a hurricane.

150
00:08:45,260 --> 00:08:48,000
If I can't move,
I'm defenseless.

151
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:51,050
I've got to find
a way to break out.

152
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:52,140
Huh?

153
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:53,230
(yelling)

154
00:08:53,230 --> 00:08:56,140
Even if an opponent avoids
the jaws of the dragon,

155
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,200
the winds of its passage
will render him helpless

156
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,170
and he'll be torn
apart by its claws.

157
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:12,030
♪

158
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:13,290
(yelling)

159
00:09:13,290 --> 00:09:23,100
♪

160
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,100
(thunderous crash)

161
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:26,070
(heavy breathing)

162
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,060
My secret fighting technique

163
00:09:31,060 --> 00:09:34,010
utilizes extreme
hand and sword speed.

164
00:09:34,010 --> 00:09:35,130
and the Hiten Mitsurugi style

165
00:09:35,130 --> 00:09:37,230
is a combination
of offense and defense.

166
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:39,090
If you combine the two,

167
00:09:39,090 --> 00:09:41,140
then you will win.

168
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:42,280
Thank you.

169
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:45,200
(rumbling)

170
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,070
You did it.

171
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:50,090
(grunting)

172
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:59,100
♪

173
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:00,190
(yells)

174
00:10:00,190 --> 00:10:02,010
♪

175
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:03,140
Well done, Kenshin.

176
00:10:03,140 --> 00:10:05,080
♪

177
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:07,230
Kenshin used his sheath fake
with his first step,

178
00:10:07,230 --> 00:10:09,220
then used his own
centrifugal force

179
00:10:09,220 --> 00:10:12,150
to obtain position
with the second step.

180
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:15,130
Then, using a double-step
crisscross technique,

181
00:10:15,130 --> 00:10:17,150
he distracted his opponent
from the true direction

182
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,230
of his sword thrust.

183
00:10:18,230 --> 00:10:20,250
The final blow used
the focused energy

184
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:22,180
of every muscle in his body.

185
00:10:22,180 --> 00:10:24,000
If Shishio survives that,

186
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,120
he must be immortal.

187
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:27,120
(grunting, gasping)

188
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:30,010
♪

189
00:10:30,010 --> 00:10:31,150
Mr. Shishio!

190
00:10:31,150 --> 00:10:47,240
♪

191
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:49,240
(yelling)

192
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:53,200
♪

193
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:56,150
Wait a second, what's
goin' on with Shishio?

194
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:57,250
I don't get it!

195
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:59,260
(yelling)

196
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:09,080
♪

197
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,130
(yelling)

198
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,170
Take it!

199
00:11:14,170 --> 00:11:16,140
(groaning, yelling)

200
00:11:31,010 --> 00:11:33,000
Ayumi, don't go!

201
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,060
(gasps)

202
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:36,240
♪

203
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:38,190
-Stop!
-What?

204
00:11:38,190 --> 00:11:40,190
Leave him alone!

205
00:11:40,190 --> 00:11:42,250
He's dying, can't you see that?

206
00:11:42,250 --> 00:11:45,290
The doctor said he could
only fight for 15 minutes.

207
00:11:45,290 --> 00:11:47,150
Once he exceeds that time limit,

208
00:11:47,150 --> 00:11:48,230
his body won't recover.

209
00:11:48,230 --> 00:11:51,090
His body heat will destroy him!

210
00:11:51,090 --> 00:11:53,160
He's no longer a danger to you.

211
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:54,260
Not anymore.

212
00:11:54,260 --> 00:11:56,160
The fighting is over.

213
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:58,230
Let me care for him...

214
00:11:58,230 --> 00:12:00,120
till he's gone.

215
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:10,170
♪

216
00:12:10,170 --> 00:12:12,170
(groaning)

217
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:14,030
It's not over.

218
00:12:14,030 --> 00:12:15,280
(screaming)

219
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:50,090
♪

220
00:12:50,090 --> 00:12:53,160
Shishio Makoto,

221
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:55,230
you're a fiend from hell.

222
00:12:55,230 --> 00:12:57,210
Only a monster could kill
the woman he loves

223
00:12:57,210 --> 00:12:59,110
in order to win a fight.

224
00:12:59,110 --> 00:13:01,210
You're not human!

225
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:03,270
What is done is done.

226
00:13:03,270 --> 00:13:07,180
You cannot judge me
by your standards, Kenshin.

227
00:13:07,180 --> 00:13:12,170
Our love is stronger now
than it ever was before.

228
00:13:12,170 --> 00:13:17,140
She's happy to have sacrificed
her life out of love for me.

229
00:13:17,140 --> 00:13:20,140
I'm so...glad...

230
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:23,020
that I could help.

231
00:13:23,020 --> 00:13:30,000
I always wanted...
to do...whatever I could

232
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:33,000
and now I've done
something to help you win

233
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,020
your greatest victory.

234
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:37,060
Oh, my love.

235
00:13:37,060 --> 00:13:41,250
I was always so jealous
of Sojiro and the others.

236
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:43,230
They could help you
to reach your goal

237
00:13:43,230 --> 00:13:45,270
to fulfill your dream

238
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:49,000
while all I could do
was tend your wounds

239
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:52,130
and give you momentary pleasure.

240
00:13:52,130 --> 00:13:56,070
But now I've helped you win
your most important battle

241
00:13:56,070 --> 00:13:58,170
and that makes me so happy.

242
00:13:58,170 --> 00:14:03,050
♪

243
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:05,160
My love...

244
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:08,260
you're the only man
I ever loved.

245
00:14:08,260 --> 00:14:10,210
♪

246
00:14:10,210 --> 00:14:16,100
You...and I...
together...

247
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,290
always.

248
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:20,010
♪

249
00:14:20,010 --> 00:14:21,090
(gasps)

250
00:14:21,090 --> 00:14:31,030
♪

251
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:32,170
Faithful Ayumi.

252
00:14:32,170 --> 00:14:33,280
She's been looking
for happiness

253
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:35,150
all of her life

254
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:40,020
and finally found it at the very
moment of her untimely death.

255
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:42,040
(groaning)

256
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:43,070
Happiness, Hoji?

257
00:14:43,070 --> 00:14:44,190
Is that what you call it?

258
00:14:44,190 --> 00:14:45,270
She didn't have to die,

259
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:47,080
she was only trying to--

260
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:49,260
(grunting)

261
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:53,280
Her death is no longer
of any importance.

262
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:57,140
The last battle
is not yet over.

263
00:14:57,140 --> 00:15:00,210
The winner has yet
to be decided.

264
00:15:00,210 --> 00:15:04,070
The strong will live
and the weak will surely die!

265
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:07,260
Only one of us will
leave this place alive.

266
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,180
Kenshin.

267
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:21,070
(gasping, heavy breathing)

268
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:42,210
♪

269
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:43,290
Huh?

270
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:47,100
♪

271
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:50,210
Why is red steam
rising off his body?

272
00:15:50,210 --> 00:15:53,040
The internal temperature
of Mr. Shishio's body

273
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,070
has risen to the level
that the coagulated blood

274
00:15:55,070 --> 00:15:58,070
from his wounds
is evaporating as steam.

275
00:15:58,070 --> 00:16:00,070
(groaning)

276
00:16:00,070 --> 00:16:11,020
♪

277
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:14,060
He's wounded so badly yet he
still has that much spirit.

278
00:16:14,060 --> 00:16:16,140
Maybe Shishio does
deserve to win.

279
00:16:16,140 --> 00:16:21,260
♪

280
00:16:21,260 --> 00:16:23,080
Kenshin!

281
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:27,240
♪

282
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:30,020
I've lost so much blood.

283
00:16:30,020 --> 00:16:32,280
All my energy seems
to be draining out of me.

284
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:35,160
My body seems so far away.

285
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,280
I can hardly feel anything.

286
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:39,250
I've been close to death before,

287
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:41,140
but never this close.

288
00:16:41,140 --> 00:16:43,030
Is this really the end?

289
00:16:43,030 --> 00:16:44,140
Is this what it feels like?

290
00:16:44,140 --> 00:16:45,270
Dying?

291
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:49,180
But can I allow myself to die
while Shishio still lives?

292
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:50,200
Yes.

293
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:52,040
Even if he survives his wounds,

294
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:54,000
it'll take him years
to recover his strength

295
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,160
and regain his power,

296
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:58,110
and by that time, others will
be strong enough to stop him.

297
00:16:58,110 --> 00:17:00,040
It's up to them now.

298
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,200
I don't think I have
it in me to go on.

299
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,270
♪

300
00:17:03,270 --> 00:17:06,010
I'm sorry I couldn't
return to Aoiya,

301
00:17:06,010 --> 00:17:08,280
sorry that I'll never see
Kori and the others again.

302
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:11,050
But I've done everything
else I set out to do.

303
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:13,150
I protected my friends
and my country.

304
00:17:13,150 --> 00:17:14,230
My duty is done.

305
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:20,160
(sobbing)

306
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:22,140
Kenshin!

307
00:17:22,140 --> 00:17:25,090
You are not allowed to give up.

308
00:17:25,090 --> 00:17:28,070
You have a task that
hasn't been completed yet.

309
00:17:28,070 --> 00:17:30,010
Quickly, wake up!

310
00:17:32,020 --> 00:17:35,010
We're going home
together, remember?

311
00:17:39,010 --> 00:17:40,150
You promised.

312
00:17:40,150 --> 00:17:47,110
♪

313
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:50,080
I solemnly swore to meet
someone who's waiting for me

314
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:52,260
and I won't break it because
of you or anyone else!

315
00:17:52,260 --> 00:17:54,240
My will to live
is stronger than you.

316
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,130
It's stronger than anything.

317
00:17:56,130 --> 00:17:58,020
The will is only as strong

318
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:00,150
as the person within
whom it abides.

319
00:18:00,150 --> 00:18:01,210
You are strong, Battousai,

320
00:18:01,210 --> 00:18:03,060
but you're not the strongest.

321
00:18:03,060 --> 00:18:04,150
As you are about to find out,

322
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:06,240
the strongest is me!

323
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:10,210
♪

324
00:18:10,210 --> 00:18:12,150
I knew you'd make
a fine meal, Kenshin.

325
00:18:12,150 --> 00:18:14,250
The time has come to eat!

326
00:18:14,250 --> 00:18:16,020
(grunting)

327
00:18:16,020 --> 00:18:17,250
Mr. Shishio's going to win.

328
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:18,220
No!

329
00:18:18,220 --> 00:18:20,280
He's gone past his limit.

330
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:23,260
(screaming)

331
00:18:46,140 --> 00:18:48,230
It just can't...be.

332
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:50,150
He's consuming himself.

333
00:18:50,150 --> 00:18:52,010
Burning from within.

334
00:18:52,010 --> 00:18:55,240
His body is using his own
fat and phosphorus as fuel.

335
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:57,210
(flames roaring)

336
00:19:00,070 --> 00:19:02,040
(gasping)

337
00:19:05,210 --> 00:19:16,250
♪

338
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:18,250
(laughing)

339
00:19:18,250 --> 00:20:01,080
♪

340
00:20:05,130 --> 00:20:07,010
(exclaiming)

341
00:20:07,010 --> 00:20:08,160
No!

342
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:10,030
I refuse to believe it!

343
00:20:10,030 --> 00:20:12,290
Shishio was winning the fight
and he should have won it!

344
00:20:12,290 --> 00:20:15,160
♪

345
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:17,040
No, Hoji.

346
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:20,130
Remember, the laws of nature
also apply to him.

347
00:20:20,130 --> 00:20:21,270
As Shishio used to say,

348
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:24,150
nature allows only
the fittest to survive.

349
00:20:24,150 --> 00:20:26,200
In this case, Kenshin.

350
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:29,080
It wasn't the time or place
for a man like Shishio

351
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:31,050
to take control.

352
00:20:31,050 --> 00:20:33,060
All his efforts,
all his plans,

353
00:20:33,060 --> 00:20:35,160
the extinction of
the Juppongatana group,

354
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:36,290
they were for nothing.

355
00:20:36,290 --> 00:20:38,230
Kenshin was merely
an instrument.

356
00:20:38,230 --> 00:20:40,200
The outcome was decided
by the ebb and flow

357
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:42,020
of history and fate,

358
00:20:42,020 --> 00:20:44,140
which would never have
allowed Shishio to succeed.

359
00:20:44,140 --> 00:20:46,120
♪

360
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:47,240
You won, pal.

361
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:50,180
♪

362
00:20:50,180 --> 00:20:51,210
Did I?

363
00:20:51,210 --> 00:20:54,030
♪

364
00:20:54,030 --> 00:20:56,100
No, he's won nothing!

365
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:58,040
Nothing, do you hear?

366
00:20:58,040 --> 00:20:59,240
I will kill you all!

367
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,210
Yes!

368
00:21:00,210 --> 00:21:03,080
You're all going to die!

369
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:04,190
Kenshin!

370
00:21:04,190 --> 00:21:05,240
Kenshin!

371
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:19,030
♪

372
00:21:19,030 --> 00:21:20,290
Damn!

373
00:21:20,290 --> 00:21:23,040
If my right hand weren't broken,
I could break down this door

374
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,290
and put Hoji out of his misery.

375
00:21:24,290 --> 00:21:27,020
We've gotta get
Kenshin out of here.

376
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:28,190
Get out of the way.

377
00:21:28,190 --> 00:21:38,110
♪

378
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:40,000
Saito.

379
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,180
Saito, don't do it.

380
00:21:41,180 --> 00:21:43,090
You'll open up your wound again.

381
00:21:43,090 --> 00:21:53,080
♪

382
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:55,000
Hey, you okay?

383
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,030
Sano, take Kenshin and Aoshi
and get out of here.

384
00:21:57,030 --> 00:21:59,010
I'll find Hoji
and take care of him.

385
00:21:59,010 --> 00:21:59,389
Go on.

386
00:21:59,389 --> 00:22:03,030
Hey...what's that?

387
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:04,080
Huh?

388
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:07,190
♪

389
00:22:07,190 --> 00:22:08,280
What in the world's that?

390
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:11,070
What the hell's goin' on?

391
00:22:11,070 --> 00:22:12,050
Die!

392
00:22:12,050 --> 00:22:13,030
Die!

393
00:22:13,030 --> 00:22:14,210
You're all gonna die!

394
00:22:14,210 --> 00:22:18,010
Mr. Shishio's enemies
are all gonna die!

395
00:22:18,010 --> 00:22:18,402
Yes!

396
00:22:18,402 --> 00:22:21,110
I'll kill you all!

397
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:24,120
And then when
you're dead and gone,

398
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:26,270
Shishio will have won!

399
00:22:26,270 --> 00:22:30,150
(explosions)

400
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:40,050
(explosion, rumbling)

401
00:22:48,190 --> 00:23:12,100
♪

402
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:14,100
(singing in foreign language)

403
00:23:14,100 --> 00:25:07,180
♪

